Author-Name: MURRAY CARLSON 
Author-Name: ALI LAZRAK 
Title: Leverage Choice and Credit Spreads when Managers Risk Shift 
Abstract:
 We model the debt and asset risk choice of a manager with
 performance-insensitive pay (cash) and performance-sensitive pay (stock)
 to theoretically link compensation structure, leverage, and credit
 spreads. The model predicts that optimal leverage trades off the tax
 benefit of debt against the utility cost of ex-post asset substitution and
 that credit spreads are increasing in the ratio of cash-to-stock. Using a
 large cross-section of U.S.-based corporate credit default swaps (CDS)
 covering 2001 to 2006, we find a positive association between
 cash-to-stock and CDS rates, and between cash-to-stock and leverage
 ratios. Copyright (c) 2010 the American Finance Association. 
